 class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529320\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529320\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kpn1665702933770.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kpn1665702933770.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kpn1665702933770.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kpn1665702933770\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Database Access on DB2\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__section_w1503ab1b5b1_w1504ab1b5_w1505ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__section_w1506ab1b5b3_w1507ab1b5_w1508ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1098435e59\">\n                        \n Logon Path\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49145e1_d49146e1_d49147e1\">In the assignment file under the [PATHS] section, enter a path in the following format:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49148e1_d49149e1_d49150e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$DB2 DB2:</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServerName</var>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49151e1_d49152e1_d49153e1\">or append it after a network path to access a DB2 database remotely:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49154e1_d49155e1_d49156e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$DB2</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Protocol</var>:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Machine</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">+</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Port</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OS-User</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OS-Password</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">+ DB2:</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServerName</var>}:{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var>}</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__li_d23972e1_d23973e1_d23974e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">ServerName</var>—name of the\n               database server <span class=\"ph\">local relational\n                  database directory entry (on iSeries)</span>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__li_d23975e1_d23976e1_d23977e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>—database name;\n               optional if a default database is specified in the ODBC DSN (Data Source Name). </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__li_d23978e1_d23979e1_d23980e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var> and\n                  <var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var>—user and password for the DB2 database. The user\n               name is not case-sensitive, but the password is. <span class=\"ph\">Optional for iSeries</span>. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49157e1_d49158e1_d49159e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pec1665702933838.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pec1665702933838.html\">Logon Path on iSeries</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__section_w1509ab1b5b5_w1510ab1b5_w1511ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1098435e187\">\n                        \n Open and Close Support\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49163e1_d49164e1_d49165e1\">Both the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> ProcScript commands are fully supported.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__section_w1512ab1b5b7_w1513ab1b5_w1514ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1098435e202\">\n                        \n Ownership\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49169e1_d49170e1_d49171e1\">Entities are created by default in a schema that is named after its creator</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49172e1_d49173e1_d49174e1\">\n<span class=\"ph\">(except on iSeries)\n </span>\n                          . If you want to access entities owned by someone else, it is probable that the tables reside in a schema named after that person, and not in your default schema. To access them, you must direct these entities in the [ENTITIES] section of the assignment file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49175e1_d49176e1_d49177e1\">In the following example, all the entities in the application model ‘FRED’ are defined as belonging to ‘JANE’:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[ENTITIES] \n*.FRED $DB2:JANE.*.* </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49178e1_d49179e1_d49180e1\">The following assignments make the tables created and owned by user USYSDB2 available to other users:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">*.DICT $DB2:USYSDB2.*.* </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kpn1665702933770__p_d49181e1_d49182e1_d49183e1\">You may want to tailor these assignments to control exactly which tables or entities users share and for which tables separate copies should be made.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnl1665702774754.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Access</a><p>Uniface automatically opens the DBMS when a read or write ProcScript statement is issued. The path and logon details for the specific database (or databases) can be provided in an assignment file, a command line instruction, or in the open ProcScript instruction.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sbg1665702735473.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Paths and Path Assignments</a><p>A path is a named route to a resource required by the application, such as a database connector and database, a remote server, or a file location.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/soa1665702524341.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>open</a><p>Open the specified DBMS or path, or connect to the Uniface Router.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifn1665702634315.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>close</a><p>Log off from the specified path or from all paths.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529320\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529320\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Database Access on DB2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Database Access on DB2 Logon Path In the assignment file under the [PATHS] section, enter a path in the following format: $DB2 DB2: { ServerName } : { Database } | { DB2UserName } | { DB2Password } or append it after a network path to access a DB2 database remotely: $DB2 Protocol : Machine + Port | OS-User | OS-Password + DB2: { ServerName }:{ Database } | { DB2UserName } | { DB2Password } ServerName —name of the database server local relational database directory entry (on iSeries) . Database —database name; optional if a default database is specified in the ODBC DSN (Data Source Name). DB2UserName and DB2Password —user and password for the DB2 database. The user name is not case-sensitive, but the password is. Optional for iSeries . For more information, see Logon Path on iSeries . Open and Close Support Both the open and close ProcScript commands are fully supported. Ownership Entities are created by default in a schema that is named after its creator (except on iSeries) . If you want to access entities owned by someone else, it is probable that the tables reside in a schema named after that person, and not in your default schema. To access them, you must direct these entities in the [ENTITIES] section of the assignment file. In the following example, all the entities in the application model ‘FRED’ are defined as belonging to ‘JANE’: [ENTITIES] *.FRED $DB2:JANE.*.* Copy The following assignments make the tables created and owned by user USYSDB2 available to other users: *.DICT $DB2:USYSDB2.*.* Copy You may want to tailor these assignments to control exactly which tables or entities users share and for which tables separate copies should be made. Related Links Database Access Uniface automatically opens the DBMS when a read or write ProcScript statement is issued. The path and logon details for the specific database (or databases) can be provided in an assignment file, a command line instruction, or in the open ProcScript instruction. Paths and Path Assignments A path is a named route to a resource required by the application, such as a database connector and database, a remote server, or a file location. open Open the specified DBMS or path, or connect to the Uniface Router. close Log off from the specified path or from all paths. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}